 Troops of Operation Thunder Strike have rescued six kidnapped students of Government Day Secondary School Gwagwada in Chikun Local Government Area of Kaduna State.  The students were abducted on their way to school on Thursday morning. The Deputy Director of Public Relations, 1 Division Nigeria Army, Kaduna, Col. Ezindu Idimah, disclosed this in Kaduna. Idimah also revealed that three motor boys were rescued while four suspected bandits were neutralised by the troops. Continue reading Army rescue six abducted students in Kaduna at Vanguard Nigeria. Source: Vanguard